Let me add tracing to the VM to find the actual bug. I'll trace the Z_Malloc call and the value passed:

{
  "analysis": "Z_Malloc is at 0x43856c. The first argument (a0=R[4]) is the size. Let me add a trap to log the call to Z_Malloc with the bad value, and trace back what computed it. The R_InitTextures function (which computes texture dimensions via multiply) is the likely source.",
  "plan": "Add a debug trap when PC reaches Z_Malloc to log the size and return address, then run briefly to capture the trace.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cp /app/vm.js /tmp/vm_work.js\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 << 'PYEOF'\nwith open('/app/vm.js','r') as f: c=f.read()\n# Add trace for Z_Malloc (0x43856c) - log size and return address (ra=R[31])\ntrace = '''  if(cpc===0x43856c){const sz=R[4]|0;if(sz<0||sz>0x4000000){console.error('Z_Malloc size='+sz+' (0x'+(sz>>>0).toString(16)+') ra=0x'+(R[31]>>>0).toString(16));}}\\n'''\nc = c.replace('  const op = I >>> 26,', trace + '  const op = I >>> 26,')\nwith open('/app/vm.js','w') as f: f.write(c)\nprint('Added trace')\nPYEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "node -c /app/vm.js && echo OK\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "timeout 40 node vm.js 2>&1 | grep -i 'Z_Malloc size' | head -5\n",
      "duration": 45.0
    }
  ]
}
